2026 Regular Session
HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 19
BY REPRESENTATIVE CHASSION
CHILDREN/LEGITIMATION: Directs the Louisiana State Law Institute to study the
presumption of parentage
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To authorize and direct the Louisiana State Law Institute to study filiation proceedings and
3 the presumption of paternity and to report its findings to the Legislature of Louisiana
4 no later than February 1, 2027.
5 WHEREAS, Civil Code Article 178 provides that filiation is the legal relationship
6 between a child and his parent; and
7 WHEREAS, Civil Code Article 179 provides that filiation is established by proof of
8 maternity or paternity or by adoption; and
9 WHEREAS, Civil Code Article 185 provides that the husband of the mother is
10 presumed to be the father of a child born during the marriage or within three hundred days
11 from the date of the termination of the marriage; and
12 WHEREAS, Civil Code Article 187 provides that the husband may disavow paternity
13 of the child by clear and convincing evidence that he is not the father; and
14 WHEREAS, Civil Code Article 190.1 provides that if blood or tissue sampling
15 indicates that the biological father is the father of the child and not the former husband, the
16 mother, biological father, and former husband may execute a three-party acknowledgment;
17 and
18 WHEREAS, if a three-party acknowledgment is executed, the former husband is not
19 presumed to be the father of the child and the biological father who has acknowledged the
20 child is the presumed father; and
