1 WHEREAS, there is no presumption of parentage if the mother is unmarried at the
2 time the child is born; and
3 WHEREAS, R.S. 9:392(A)(3) provides that if the alleged father does not
4 acknowledge the child, the mother has the right to file a paternity suit to establish paternity;
5 and
6 WHEREAS, the presumption of paternity could cause harm to families; and
7 WHEREAS, many families cannot afford court costs to establish paternity and suing
8 to establish paternity could be an undue burden; and
9 WHEREAS, it may be in the best interest of Louisiana families to not have a
10 presumption of paternity.
11 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
12 authorize and direct the Louisiana State Law Institute to study filiation and the presumption
13 of paternity to determine if it is feasible to remove the presumption of paternity and to report
14 its findings to the Legislature of Louisiana no later than February 1, 2027.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
16 director of the Louisiana State Law Institute.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Louisiana State Law Institute shall submit
18 one printed copy and one electronic copy of any report produced pursuant to this Resolution
19 to the David R. Poynter Legislative Research Library as required by R.S. 24:772.
